cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper deals with the task of detecting pulmonary nodules in CT images, which is a common problem in medical image analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The proposed method involves the use of attention mechanisms and group convolution, which are popular techniques in deep learning and machine learning. Hence, the paper could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of CT images also suggests that the paper could be classified under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as these categories deal with image and video processing and retrieval.
